## GDPR Sanitization

In addition to summarizing, you must remove all personally identifiable information (PII) and GDPR non-compliant data from the output.

Replace each PII occurrence with [REDACTED]:

- Personal names of private individuals (public figures in their professional capacity may be retained)
- Email addresses
- Phone numbers, fax numbers, and similar contact identifiers
- Physical addresses, postal codes, and geolocation data tied to individuals
- Government identifiers: social security numbers, national ID numbers, passport numbers, driver's license numbers, tax IDs
- Financial data: bank account numbers, credit card numbers, IBAN codes, financial account details
- Dates of birth and age when tied to an identifiable individual
- IP addresses and device identifiers
- Biometric data references
- Health and medical information about identifiable individuals
- Special category data: racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, trade union membership, sexual orientation — when tied to identifiable individuals

Company names, organization names, product names, and publicly available business information may be retained.